
---


@startuml

' Set skinparam for better readability
skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor white
    BorderColor black
    ArrowColor black
}

' Define classes
class User {
    - id: String (unique)
    - name: String
    - email: String
    - dateOfBirth: Date
    + createAccount(accountType: String): Account
}

class Account {
    - accountNumber: String (auto-generated, unique)
    - accountType: String (Personal or Business)
    - user: User (1-1)
    + createPage(name: String): Page
    + grantPrivilege(page: Page, otherAccount: PersonalAccount): void
}

class PersonalAccount extends Account {
    + sendFriendRequest(toUser: User): void
    + receiveFriendRequest(fromUser: User): void
}

class BusinessAccount extends Account {
    - companyName: String
    - monthlyFee: Decimal
}

class Page {
    - pageName: String
    - visits: Integer
    - adminAccount: Account (1-1)
    + updateVisits(): void
}

class AdvertisementPage extends Page {
    - bounceRate: Double
    - clickThroughRate: Double
    - conversionRate: Double
}

' Associations and Relationships
User "1" -- "0..*" Account : owns
Account "1" -- "0..*" Page : creates
Page "1" -- "0..*" AdvertisementPage : extends
Account "1" -- "0..1" PersonalAccount : if type == "Personal"
Account "1" -- "0..1" BusinessAccount : if type == "Business"

' Note about multiple accounts restriction
note right of User
    A user cannot have more than one account (either personal or business).
end note

@enduml

---

### 📌 Key Points Captured in the Diagram:

- **User** has a unique ID and can create only **one** account.
- **Account** is identified by an auto-generated number and is linked to a **User**.
- Two types of accounts:
  - **PersonalAccount**: Can send/receive friend requests.
  - **BusinessAccount**: Has company name and monthly fee.
- **Page** is managed by exactly one **Account**, and each **Account** can't have duplicate page names.
- **AdvertisementPage** is a special type of **Page** with metrics like bounce rate, CTR, and conversion rate.
- **Privileges** can be granted between **PersonalAccounts** and **Pages**.
- **Multiple accounts per user is not allowed**, enforced via a note.

